Still  one could save the day without being too optimistic in any dovish tone.After all  inflation remains elevated  and the route to normalcy could still be distant.ğŸ“¦Employment cost is moderatingğŸ“ŠWe also saw a green shoot on Tuesdayâ€™s data. The Employment Cost Index (QoQ) came in at 1.0%  a drop from 1.2% in the prior period and lower than the forecast of 1.1%. This is good news as slowing labour compensation growth can help reduce disposable income  promoting lesser demand for goods and alleviating demand-pull inflation.It is precisely what the Fed wishes to see and a day before the FOMC is welcoming.
